============================================================
CURRENT STATUS — PARTIALLY COMPILED
============================================================

Some subdirectories (Display, Utils, AppBundle, SwiftSignalKit, Markdown,
GZip, Svg, ManagedFile, etc.) are still compiled into the Octo iOS build
because WKMessageCell and related chat UI depend on:

  - ContextControllerSourceNode (long-press source node)
  - ContextExtractedContentContainingNode (content container)
  - TapLongTapOrDoubleTapGestureRecognizer (custom gesture state machine)
  - ContextGesture (UIGestureRecognizer subclass with beginDelay)

These custom gesture/node types coordinate correctly with
UINavigationController.interactivePopGestureRecognizer and UIScrollView's
panGestureRecognizer. Naive UIKit replacements (UILongPressGestureRecognizer
+ UITapGestureRecognizer) cause back-swipe failures and tableview scrolling
issues. Replacing them properly requires reimplementing the custom gesture
state machine, which is non-trivial.

Other subdirectories are excluded via WuKongBase.podspec exclude_files
(see README.md in this directory for the list and reasons).

============================================================
LICENSE COMPATIBILITY NOTICE
============================================================

Because GPL v2 code is linked into the Octo iOS application binary, the
license obligations of GPL v2 apply to the portions of the project that
link against this code. Anyone distributing built binaries of Octo iOS
must comply with GPL v2 terms for those portions.

If your use case requires fully Apache 2.0 (e.g., commercial closed-source),
you must first replace the active Telegram-derived code listed above with
your own implementation. Contributions toward that goal are welcome.

